        "timestamp": "2019-03-14 10:54:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nYou appear to be trying to use the Builder Pattern, however the implementation does not conform to one, since the builder class does not have a build method that returns the object you are trying to build.\n\nWhat you have actually implemented appears to be a POJO-like class with special setters that returns itself, and using that to pass multiple values into a method call.\n\nI recommend that you either convert your new class into a regular POJO and use it as a simple data object which wraps the input parameters, or implement the builder pattern in earnest to create a builder that can be used to build a SpikeEventEntity object directly.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
